In [36]:
def predict(data, train_df, forecast_val):
    # set the uncertainty interval to 95% (the Prophet default is 80%)
    dff = train_df.rename(columns={'date': 'ds','quantity_bought': 'y'})
    
    model = Prophet(daily_seasonality=False, weekly_seasonality=False, seasonality_prior_scale=.2)
    
    for regressor in add_regressors:
        model.add_regressor(regressor)
    
    model.fit(dff)
    future_dates = model.make_future_dataframe(periods=forecast_val, freq='15 min')
    
    for regressor in add_regressors:
        future_dates[regressor] = data[regressor]
            
    forecast = model.predict(future_dates)
    return model, forecast
